713918f.title: Manhattan: 57th Street (West) - 9th Avenue
713918f.text:
353-361 West 57th Street (excavation), adjoining the N.E. corner of
Ninth Ave., showing the clearance through to 58th Street upon which
stands the 26 and 35-storied American Womans Association Building. The
view is northwestward and shows in the left background the side walls of
the 5-story tenements that face on the east side of Tenth Ave., between
57th and 58th Streets. The structures seen through the open space are
buildings on the north side of West 58th Street, east of Ninth Ave.
This set consists of a negative and a positive.
October 22, 1927.
Gift of Albert A. Volk Co.

713928f-b.title: Manhattan: 57th Street (West) - 9th Avenue
713928f-b.text:
(1)
West 57th Street, north side, at Ninth Avenue (elevated line
thereon), showing adjoining the N.E. corner of same, a demolition
that includes No's. 353 to 361 inclusive and extends thru the block
to 58th Street. Upon this site will rise the American Women's
Association Bldg. The photographer is viewing north westward from
a point between Eighth and Ninth Avenues.
Sept. 22, 1927
P. L. Sperr
(2)
A portion of this site slightly later, showing the form-r buildings
leveled to the ground. The photographer here is viewing north eastward
to 58th Street upon which appears the buildings shown.
Oct. 22, 1927
P. L. Sperr
